      "content": "i see, so it's a very specific aesthetic. but what about if someone is in a place where those styles aren't the norm? like if they're in parts of asia or africa where people might dress more colorfully or follow different social customs during business dinners? should they stick to the navy/charcoal/leather shoe look to stay professional, or is it okay to incorporate those local styles? i want to make sure my readers know if they'll look \"low-class\" if they don't follow the western standard.",
